{"key":"post-8800001","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8800001</id>\n<content>Get a blower in the 500 to 600 cfm range @ 1&quot; static pressure.&amp;nbsp; You want an air speed of +/- 100 to 125 feet per minute leaving the face of the filter, so with 4 square feet, 400 cubic feet per minute of airflow would give you 100 linear feet per minute out the front assuming 100% efficiency.&amp;nbsp; However, you'll never get 100%, so add an extra 20% or so to cover losses from friction, turns, etc.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8802998</next>\n<prev>8799826</prev>\n<first>8795157</first>\n<last>8802998</last>\n<when>1219241903</when>\n<utime>08/20/08 05:18 PM</utime>\n</post>"}